Business model
Details
C.H. Robinson
Freight Forwarding
C.H. Robinson is implementing "Lean AI" with over 30 connected AI agents automating quote-to-cash
processes, driving 40%+ productivity gains since 2022, enabling double-digit productivity increases, and
contributing to market share growth and gross margin expansion.
COSCO SHIPPING
Container Shipping, Ports
COSCO SHIPPING Ports is implementing AI through unmanned container truck operations at 5 terminals,
achieving 10% cost reduction per container and 69% growth in operational volume to 530,000 TEUs, with
plans for AI applications in maintenance, security, asset utilization, and environmental monitoring.
DHL
Express Delivery, Freight Forwarding,
Supply Chain / Warehousing
DHL is deploying Agentic AI across multiple areas including frontline recruiting, customer service,
customs classification, and service logistics dispatch calls, with technology investments continuing at
similar levels to previous years as part of their organic investment strategy.
Fedex
Express delivery
FedEx is leveraging AI across operations and customer services, with deep learning models enhancing
predictability, enabling Network 2.0 implementation, and powering premium monitoring tools for
healthcare customers.
Freightos
Brokerage
Freightos is using AI to improve customer support efficiency, with benefits already visible in handling
more transactions without proportional increases in personnel costs, though specific financial impacts
and future expectations are not detailed.
GXO
Supply Chain / Warehousing
GXO is leveraging AI through their GXO IQ platform developed with Google Cloud for supply chain
operations, using AI for reverse logistics to rapidly resell returned products, proactive replenishment
tools, and warehouse AI advances that have increased automated revenue processing to 50%. It is
deploying AI across operations with 8 proprietary AI modules for volume forecasting and proactive
replenishment, using GXO IQ platform for rollout, and applying AI to corporate functions like HR, IT and
finance to improve overhead efficiency and cost to serve.
J.B. Hunt
Brokerage
J.B. Hunt has deployed 50 AI agents across their business to automate tasks and streamline operations,
achieving significant automation milestones including 60% automated carrier check calls, 73% auto-
accepted orders, 80% automated invoice processing, and 100,000+ automated hours annually across
Highway, Dedicated and CE teams.
JD Logistics
Freight Forwarding, Supply Chain /
Warehousing
JD Logistics uses AI across warehousing, transportation, and delivery operations through robots,
automated equipment, and large language models to drive cost savings and efficiency improvements,
with ongoing R&D investments of RMB 1.06 billion in Q3 2025.
Kuehne + Nagel
Freight Forwarding, Supply Chain /
Warehousing
Kuehne + Nagel is in early stages of AI adoption, focusing on large language models and digital agents
to reduce cost-to-serve, though specific use cases, financial impacts, and investment amounts are not
detailed in the document.
Landstar
Brokerage
Landstar is implementing AI in three key areas: agent assistance with suggested pricing, BCO retention
analytics to predict driver departures, and customer service automation to improve efficiency and
effectiveness when serving BCOs and agents.
Ryder
Truck Freight
Ryder is deploying Agentic AI technologies to improve service levels and effectiveness in transportation
management and brokerage, optimizing rates for customers, improving service levels, and enhancing
freight bill audit and pay activities across supply chain, fleet management, and dedicated business
segments.
UPS
Express Delivery, Supply Chain /
Warehousing
UPS is implementing Agentic AI to streamline customs brokerage processes, enabling digital processing
of over 90% of cross-border transactions and handling a tenfold surge in daily customs entries following
trade policy changes.
RXO
Freight forwarding, Supply chain
management
Agentic AI to schedule, communicate with truckers and track shipment progress. This process only
escalates live leads or critical situations to a human operator, freeing up tens of thousands of man
hours. Management believes that they may never have to hire people for some roles again and as AI
takes over more functions their existing employees can move up the value curve into more relationship
forward functions.
